<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">

<%- include('../partials/head') %>

  <body>
    <%- include('../partials/header') %>

      <main>
        <section class="hero">
          <div class="container hero-grid">
            <div class="hero-copy">
              <h1>CollectIn — LinkedIn Saved Posts Collection</h1>
              <p class="lead">Organize your LinkedIn saved posts into collections, just like you would do in Instagram.
              </p>
              <div class="cta-row">
                <a class="button primary large" href="#">Add to Chrome</a>
              </div>
            </div>

            <video width="100%" height="auto" autoplay muted playsinline loop class="hero-video">
              <source src="assets/full-demo.webm" type="video/mp4">
              Your browser does not support the video tag.
            </video>

          </div>
        </section>

        <section id="features" class="features">
          <div class="container">
            <h2>Everything you need for tidy saves</h2>
            <div class="feature-grid">
              <div class="feature">
                <div class="icon">🗂️</div>
                <h3>Organize saved posts into collections</h3>
                <p>Turn your LinkedIn saves into neatly labeled collections for faster retrieval.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="feature">
                <div class="icon">🏷️</div>
                <h3>Inline collection badges</h3>
                <p>See a pill on each saved post showing its collection; click to reassign in seconds.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="feature">
                <div class="icon">⚡</div>
                <h3>Collection filters and quick creation</h3>
                <p>Browse by any collection or view all posts with instant filter switching. Create new collections on
                  the
                  fly using the "+" pill in LinkedIn's filter bar.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="feature">
                <div class="icon">🔒</div>
                <h3>Private, local storage</h3>
                <p>Your collections and posts are saved in your browser's storage—no account required.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="feature">
                <div class="icon">🧩</div>
                <h3>Native LinkedIn experience</h3>
                <p>Designed to blend with LinkedIn's UI on linkedin.com for a seamless workflow.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section id="how-it-works" class="how-section">
          <div class="container">
            <div class="section-header">
              <h2>How it works</h2>
            </div>
            <div class="steps-grid">
              <div class="step">
                <div class="step-icon-container">
                  <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="32" height="32" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"
                    stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"
                    class="step-icon">
                    <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"></circle>
                    <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="4"></circle>
                    <line x1="21.17" y1="8" x2="12" y2="8"></line>
                    <line x1="3.95" y1="6.06" x2="8.54" y2="14"></line>
                    <line x1="10.88" y1="21.94" x2="15.46" y2="14"></line>
                  </svg>
                </div>
                <h3 class="step-title">1. Install the Extension</h3>
                <p class="step-description">
                  Add CollectIn to your browser from the Chrome Web Store with just one click.
                </p>
              </div>
              <div class="step">
                <div class="step-icon-container">
                  <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="32" height="32" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"
                    stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"
                    class="step-icon">
                    <path d="M16 8a6 6 0 0 1 6 6v7h-4v-7a2 2 0 0 0-2-2 2 2 0 0 0-2 2v7h-4v-7a6 6 0 0 1 6-6z"></path>
                    <rect width="4" height="12" x="2" y="9"></rect>
                    <circle cx="4" cy="4" r="2"></circle>
                  </svg>
                </div>
                <h3 class="step-title">2. Browse LinkedIn</h3>
                <p class="step-description">
                  Continue using LinkedIn as normal. When you save a post, you'll be prompted to add it to a collection.
                </p>
              </div>
              <div class="step">
                <div class="step-icon-container">
                  <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="32" height="32" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"
                    stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"
                    class="step-icon">
                    <path d="M19 21H5a2 2 0 0 1-2-2V5a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h11l5 5v11a2 2 0 0 1-2 2z"></path>
                    <polyline points="17 21 17 13 7 13 7 21"></polyline>
                    <polyline points="7 3 7 8 15 8"></polyline>
                  </svg>
                </div>
                <h3 class="step-title">3. Organize</h3>
                <p class="step-description">
                  Filter by collection in the saved posts and articles page to find posts quickly. Create new
                  collections
                  using the "+" pill in LinkedIn's filter bar.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="cta">
          <div class="container cta-box">
            <h2>Get organized in minutes</h2>
            <p>Install the extension and bring order to your LinkedIn saves.</p>
            <a class="button primary large" href="#">Add to Chrome</a>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section id="faq" class="faq">
          <div class="container">
            <h2>FAQ</h2>
            <div class="faq-grid">
              <article>
                <h3>Does this change my LinkedIn account?</h3>
                <p>No. It visually augments the Saved page in your browser. Nothing is posted to your profile.</p>
              </article>
              <article>
                <h3>Is it free?</h3>
                <p>Yes. The core features are free.</p>
              </article>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>
      </main>

      <%- include('../partials/footer') %>
  </body>

</html>